const eleventyNavigation = {
	key: "Home",
	order: 1
};

const numberOfLatestPostsToShow = 3;
---
<p>I found 11ty really useful to update my site easily, without friction, so I’m in that process of making it all work. I want to prioritize creating content over aesthetics. But if you’re curious to see what a build from scratch with mild attention to looks feels like, my old site is still up. Feel free to check it out <a href="https://psantalla.github.io/pablosantalla.com/" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
<p>Otherwise, you’re welcome to stick around and maybe stumble across an unpainted wall or two.</p>
{% set postsCount = collections.posts | length %}
{% set latestPostsCount = postsCount | min(numberOfLatestPostsToShow) %}
<h1>Latest {{ latestPostsCount }} Post{% if latestPostsCount != 1 %}s{% endif %}</h1>

{% set postslist = collections.posts | head(-1 * numberOfLatestPostsToShow) %}
{% set postslistCounter = postsCount %}
{% include "postslist.njk" %}

{% set morePosts = postsCount - numberOfLatestPostsToShow %}
{% if morePosts > 0 %}
<p>{{ morePosts }} more post{% if morePosts != 1 %}s{% endif %} can be found in <a href="blog.njk">the archive</a>.</p>
{% endif %}

